article.description: Chris Clemons had 32 points as Campbell topped South Carolina Upstate 85-73 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Clemons scores 32 to lift Campbell over SC-Upstate 85-73
article.linkText: Clemons scores 32 to lift Campbell over SC-Upstate 85-73
article.story: SPARTANBURG, S.C. -- Chris Clemons had 32 points as Campbell topped South Carolina Upstate 85-73 on Wednesday night. Ja'Cor Nelson had 17 points for Campbell (18-11, 11-4 Big South Conference). Andrew Eudy added 15 points, 10 rebounds and four blocks. Cory Gensler had six rebounds for the visiting team. Deion Holmes had 22 points and eight rebounds for the Spartans (6-24, 1-15), who have now lost seven games in a row. Everette Hammond scored a season-high 20 points and had six rebounds. The Fighting Camels improve to 2-0 against the Spartans on the season. Campbell defeated South Carolina Upstate 82-66 on Feb. 9. Campbell finishes out the regular season against Radford at home on Saturday. South Carolina Upstate finishes out the regular season against Hampton at home on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
